From: Pooventhiran G <pooventh@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 8 Jul 2025 12:11:36 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 04/13] AP MLD: Validate Link Reconfiguration Request frame
 after parsing

When a Link Reconfiguration Request frame is successfully parsed, and
setup with context, validate the request to verify links requested for
operation(s) are valid.

While at it, if accepting the request after current validation tends to
leave the ML Setup with zero links, recover from the situation by
rejecting a "delete" link request. Currently, the "delete" link request
with the lowest link ID will be rejected.

Reviewed-by: Rohan Dutta <drohan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Pooventhiran G <pooventh@qti.qualcomm.com>
